This paper discusses the optimization landscape and expressivity of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the importance of depth and width in deep learning, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on CNNs and their features suggests relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes topics such as natural language processing and speech recognition that also use CNNs.
